			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">The information below is out-dated, instead of deleting it I am going to eventually move it to an archive thread.</span>
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I conducted these tests at level 58, with the same equipment through all three tests.  All three tests were preformed using Shock Of Steal (SoS), which I am specialized in.
<br />

<br />
Through all of these tests I had 196 Int.
<br />

<br />
Knowing that spells always require the full mana cost of the spell be availible before you are allowed to cast, SoS took 11% of my mana to cast.  This of course meant I had 2500 Mana.  Double checking this on a mana calc and it indeed did come too 2509 mana. This value was constant throughout all the tests.
<br />

<br />
I had no mana regen or other buffs whatsoever throughout the tests.  Each test was performed 100 times each.  Below are averages of the 100 tests.
<br />

<br />
Specialization + SCM 1 = 9.6%
<br />
9.6% = 240 Mana which yields 35 mana in savings.
<br />
Specialization saved 10-11% or 28 mana, which means SCM 1 = 7 mana off which means SCM 1 = 2.5% savings.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Final Conclusion</span>: SCM 1 gives 2.5% mana cost reduction.
<br />

<br />
Specialization + SCM 2 = 8.9%
<br />
8.9% = 223 Mana which yields 52 mana in savings.
<br />
Specialization saved 10-11% or 28 Mana, which means SCM 2 = 24 mana or 8.7%.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Final Conclusion</span>: SCM 2 gives 8.7% mana cost reduction.
<br />

<br />
Specialization + SCM 3 = 8.3%
<br />
8.3% = 208 Mana which yields 67 mana savings.
<br />
Specialization saved 10-11% or 28 mana, which means SCM 3 = 39 mana or 14.2%.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Final Conclusion</span>: SCM 3 gives 14.2% mana cost reduction 
<br />

<br />
The numbers did not fluxuate beyond inconsequential amounts during the tests.  Certainly not enough to infer that the checks are random, but enough to show the new UI Updates a little slowly.  Essentially, given the mathmatical steps throughout this trial my final conlusion puts SCM as a constant savings as listed below:
<br />

<br />
SCM 1 = 2.5% 
<br />
SCM 2 = 7.5%
<br />
SCM 3 = 15%
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Special thanks to Solovey for originally compiling this information</span><br />_________________<br /><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="left"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26797"><img src="http://www.jtbates.net/everquest/images/jtshieldtransparent.gif" border="0" /></a></td><td><a href="http://www.fohguild.org">[Fires of Heaven]</a> - <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3239">[Magician's Tower Library]</a></td></tr><tr><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">Join us in serverwide.magicians:fluffy</span></span></tr></table><br>
