			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">(<span style="font-weight: bold">1</span>) The text from SCM states that your chance to "succeed a specialization check" are increased by 5%, 15%, and 30% for each level.
<br />

<br />
If succeeding on a specialization check yields a half-cost spell (guess), and a specialization skill of 200 gives a base 50% chance (guess) to "specialize"....
<br />

<br />

<br />
400 mana cost spell == 200 cost (half time) + 400 cost (half time) == 300 cost average.  25% savings  -- this is the base perspective, from which people witness "mana savings" from SCM.
<br />

<br />
if SCM3 increases the "chance to specialize" to 65% (50% + 30% * 50%), your average mana cost on a "400 mana" spell will be:
<br />

<br />
200 cost (2/3rds of the time) + 400 cost (1/3rd of the time) ==
<br />
266 cost (average).
<br />

<br />
300/266 = 12.8% savings over no SCM.
<br />

<br />
I would wager that my numbers are not only close, but even "right on".  The designers who created these formulae are human, and have a strong tendancy to use "halves" and "thirds", amongst other convenient values.
<br />

<br />
With this, I would theorize that the savings, with SCM3, on non-specialization (50 skill) spells is:
<br />

<br />
400 mana cost * (theory states 1/8 chance of having cost at 50 skill)
<br />
200 mana (1/8th of the time) + 400 mana (7/8ths of the time) ==
<br />
375 mana (average)... ~7% savings with no SCM
<br />

<br />
SCM3 should increase these chances to (12.5% * 30% + 12.5% == 16.25% chance to halve cost).
<br />

<br />
Thus, the 400 mana spell should cost:
<br />
(16.25% 200 cost + 83.75% 400 cost) 367.5 mana average cost ... ~9% savings overall, and about 2% difference from no SCM.
<br />

<br />
--------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
(<span style="font-weight: bold">2</span>) Another theory is that Spec: 200 gives about 40% overall chance to halve mana cost, and the "+30%" from SCM3 is added directly.  If this is the case, we should see a much greater improvement from the ~10% savings that would be given on the 50 skill specializations, as they would improve to 40%...  This would provide a lot more benefit from SCM to casters overall.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Arhallia Ironborne</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">Alliance of the Arcane</span></span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Quellious server</span></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Arhallia on Tue Dec 16, 2003 10:09 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
